Key Match Events: Victor Wembanyama tallied six points, four rebounds, one assist, one block, and four turnovers in 14 minutes.
Dallas Mavericks backup center Dereck Lively II finished with six points, five rebounds, one steal, and one block.
The Dallas Mavericks broke the game open in the fourth quarter by unleashing a demoralizing 19-5 run in the first four minutes.
San Antonio Spurs coach Gregg Popovich took Victor Wembanyama out of the game with 5:59 remaining and the Mavericks holding a 111-90 lead.
Dallas Mavericks cruised to a 120-109 win.
